---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Prime Spirals — Math Explorations | Hayaan Dangra"
  description="Interactive Ulam spiral visualization revealing hidden diagonal patterns in prime number distribution."
>
  <section class="demo-page section">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Prime Spirals: The Ulam Spiral</h1>

      <div class="explanation">
        <p>This one started because I read that a guy named Ulam was bored in a meeting in 1963, started writing numbers in a spiral, and circled the primes. They lined up. Diagonals everywhere. I didn't believe it, so I built this to check.</p>
        <p>Primes are supposed to be the most random thing in math. There's no formula that generates all of them. So why do they line up when you just... arrange numbers in a spiral? I still don't have a good answer, and apparently neither does anyone else.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="demo-container">
        <h2>Ulam Spiral</h2>
        <div class="canvas-wrapper">
          <canvas id="primesCanvas"></canvas>
        </div>

        <div class="controls">
          <div class="control-group">
            <label for="gridSlider">
              Grid Size: <span id="gridValue">100</span> × <span id="gridValue2">100</span>
            </label>
            <input type="range" id="gridSlider" min="50" max="200" step="10" value="100">
          </div>

          <div class="control-row">
            <div class="checkbox-group">
              <input type="checkbox" id="showNumbers" disabled>
              <label for="showNumbers">Show numbers (small grids only)</label>
            </div>

            <div class="checkbox-group">
              <input type="checkbox" id="highlightDiagonals">
              <label for="highlightDiagonals">Highlight diagonals</label>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="control-group">
            <label for="colorScheme">Color Scheme:</label>
            <select id="colorScheme">
              <option value="classic">Classic (Black & White)</option>
              <option value="heat">Heat Map</option>
            </select>
          </div>

          <button id="resetBtn">Reset</button>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="why-matters">
        <h2>The Rabbit Hole I Went Down</h2>
        <p>Once I saw the diagonals, I had to know why. Turns out those lines correspond to quadratic polynomials — like n² + n + 41, which spits out 40 primes in a row before it misses. I tried plugging in n = 0 through 39 by hand, and every single one was prime. That felt like a glitch in the matrix.</p>
        <p>What I can't get over is that nobody fully understands why this works. Primes are the building blocks of all numbers, and we still can't explain their patterns. I keep coming back to this demo and zooming out to bigger grids, looking for more structure.</p>
      </div>

      <nav class="demo-nav">
        <a href="/math-explorations/chaos">← Chaos Theory</a>
        <a href="/math-explorations/walks">Next: Random Walks →</a>
      </nav>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .demo-page {
    padding: var(--space-xl) 0 var(--space-3xl);
  }

  h1 {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }

  h2 {
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .explanation {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto var(--space-2xl);
    background-color: var(--light-gray);
    padding: var(--space-lg);
    border-radius: 8px;
    border-left: 4px solid var(--orange);
  }

  .demo-container {
    max-width: 1000px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .canvas-wrapper {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  }

  canvas {
    border: 1px solid var(--mid-gray);
    border-radius: 4px;
    background-color: var(--white);
    max-width: 100%;
    height: auto;
  }

  .controls {
    margin: var(--space-lg) 0;
    padding: var(--space-md);
    background-color: var(--light-gray);
    border-radius: 8px;
  }

  .control-group {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .control-group:last-of-type {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .control-row {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-lg);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .checkbox-group {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--space-xs);
  }

  .checkbox-group input[type="checkbox"] {
    width: 20px;
    height: 20px;
    cursor: pointer;
  }

  .checkbox-group input[type="checkbox"]:disabled {
    cursor: not-allowed;
    opacity: 0.5;
  }

  .checkbox-group label {
    margin: 0;
    cursor: pointer;
    font-weight: 400;
  }

  label {
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--charcoal);
  }

  #gridValue, #gridValue2 {
    color: var(--orange);
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  input[type="range"] {
    width: 100%;
    height: 8px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    background: var(--mid-gray);
    outline: none;
    -webkit-appearance: none;
  }

  input[type="range"]::-webkit-slider-thumb {
    -webkit-appearance: none;
    appearance: none;
    width: 20px;
    height: 20px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--orange);
    cursor: pointer;
  }

  input[type="range"]::-moz-range-thumb {
    width: 20px;
    height: 20px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--orange);
    cursor: pointer;
    border: none;
  }

  select {
    width: 100%;
    padding: var(--space-sm);
    border: 1px solid var(--mid-gray);
    border-radius: 4px;
    background-color: var(--white);
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 1rem;
    cursor: pointer;
  }

  button {
    min-width: 120px;
    min-height: 44px;
  }

  .why-matters {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: var(--space-2xl) auto;
    padding: var(--space-lg);
    background-color: var(--light-gray);
    border-radius: 8px;
    border-left: 4px solid var(--blue);
  }

  .demo-nav {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: var(--space-md);
    margin-top: var(--space-2xl);
    padding-top: var(--space-xl);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--mid-gray);
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .demo-nav a {
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .control-row {
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: var(--space-sm);
    }

    .demo-nav {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: center;
    }
  }
</style>

<script>
  const canvas = document.getElementById('primesCanvas') as HTMLCanvasElement;
  const gridSlider = document.getElementById('gridSlider') as HTMLInputElement;
  const gridValue = document.getElementById('gridValue') as HTMLSpanElement;
  const gridValue2 = document.getElementById('gridValue2') as HTMLSpanElement;
  const showNumbers = document.getElementById('showNumbers') as HTMLInputElement;
  const highlightDiagonals = document.getElementById('highlightDiagonals') as HTMLInputElement;
  const colorScheme = document.getElementById('colorScheme') as HTMLSelectElement;
  const resetBtn = document.getElementById('resetBtn') as HTMLButtonElement;

  function isPrime(n: number): boolean {
    if (n < 2) return false;
    if (n === 2) return true;
    if (n % 2 === 0) return false;

    const sqrt = Math.sqrt(n);
    for (let i = 3; i <= sqrt; i += 2) {
      if (n % i === 0) return false;
    }
    return true;
  }

  function drawUlamSpiral() {
    const gridSize = parseInt(gridSlider.value);
    gridValue.textContent = gridSize.toString();
    gridValue2.textContent = gridSize.toString();

    // Enable "Show numbers" only for small grids
    if (gridSize <= 70) {
      showNumbers.disabled = false;
    } else {
      showNumbers.disabled = true;
      showNumbers.checked = false;
    }

    const cellSize = Math.min(600 / gridSize, 10);
    const canvasSize = gridSize * cellSize;

    canvas.width = canvasSize;
    canvas.height = canvasSize;

    const ctx = canvas.getContext('2d')!;
    ctx.fillStyle = '#FFFFFF';
    ctx.fillRect(0, 0, canvasSize, canvasSize);

    // Generate spiral coordinates
    const spiral: { x: number; y: number; n: number }[] = [];
    let x = Math.floor(gridSize / 2);
    let y = Math.floor(gridSize / 2);
    let dx = 0;
    let dy = -1;
    let n = 1;

    for (let i = 0; i < gridSize * gridSize; i++) {
      if (x >= 0 && x < gridSize && y >= 0 && y < gridSize) {
        spiral.push({ x, y, n });
      }

      if (x === y || (x < 0 && x === -y) || (x > 0 && x === 1 - y)) {
        const temp = dx;
        dx = -dy;
        dy = temp;
      }

      x += dx;
      y += dy;
      n++;
    }

    // Draw primes
    const scheme = colorScheme.value;

    // Pre-compute prime grid for heat map mode (avoids O(n²) filtering)
    const primeGrid: boolean[][] = [];
    if (scheme === 'heat') {
      for (let i = 0; i < gridSize; i++) {
        primeGrid[i] = new Array(gridSize).fill(false);
      }
      spiral.forEach(({ x, y, n }) => {
        if (x >= 0 && x < gridSize && y >= 0 && y < gridSize) {
          primeGrid[x][y] = isPrime(n);
        }
      });
    }

    spiral.forEach(({ x, y, n }) => {
      const prime = isPrime(n);

      if (scheme === 'classic') {
        ctx.fillStyle = prime ? '#2C3E50' : '#F8F9FA';
      } else {
        // Heat map: color by local prime density using pre-computed grid
        let neighbors = 0;
        for (let dx = -1; dx <= 1; dx++) {
          for (let dy = -1; dy <= 1; dy++) {
            const nx = x + dx;
            const ny = y + dy;
            if (nx >= 0 && nx < gridSize && ny >= 0 && ny < gridSize && primeGrid[nx][ny]) {
              neighbors++;
            }
          }
        }

        if (prime) {
          const intensity = Math.min(255, neighbors * 40);
          ctx.fillStyle = `rgb(${255 - intensity}, ${100 + intensity / 2}, ${intensity})`;
        } else {
          ctx.fillStyle = '#F8F9FA';
        }
      }

      ctx.fillRect(x * cellSize, y * cellSize, cellSize, cellSize);

      // Show numbers on small grids
      if (showNumbers.checked && cellSize >= 8) {
        ctx.fillStyle = prime ? '#FFFFFF' : '#2C3E50';
        ctx.font = `${cellSize * 0.4}px DM Sans`;
        ctx.textAlign = 'center';
        ctx.textBaseline = 'middle';
        ctx.fillText(n.toString(), x * cellSize + cellSize / 2, y * cellSize + cellSize / 2);
      }
    });

    // Highlight diagonals
    if (highlightDiagonals.checked) {
      ctx.strokeStyle = 'rgba(230, 126, 34, 0.3)';
      ctx.lineWidth = 2;

      // Draw main diagonal lines
      for (let i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
        ctx.beginPath();
        const angle = (Math.PI / 4) + (i * Math.PI / 2);
        const length = canvasSize * 0.7;
        const centerX = canvasSize / 2;
        const centerY = canvasSize / 2;
        const startX = centerX - Math.cos(angle) * length / 2;
        const startY = centerY - Math.sin(angle) * length / 2;
        const endX = centerX + Math.cos(angle) * length / 2;
        const endY = centerY + Math.sin(angle) * length / 2;
        ctx.moveTo(startX, startY);
        ctx.lineTo(endX, endY);
        ctx.stroke();
      }
    }

    // Draw grid lines for larger cells
    if (cellSize >= 5) {
      ctx.strokeStyle = 'rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05)';
      ctx.lineWidth = 1;
      for (let i = 0; i <= gridSize; i++) {
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.moveTo(i * cellSize, 0);
        ctx.lineTo(i * cellSize, canvasSize);
        ctx.stroke();

        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.moveTo(0, i * cellSize);
        ctx.lineTo(canvasSize, i * cellSize);
        ctx.stroke();
      }
    }
  }

  gridSlider.addEventListener('input', drawUlamSpiral);
  showNumbers.addEventListener('change', drawUlamSpiral);
  highlightDiagonals.addEventListener('change', drawUlamSpiral);
  colorScheme.addEventListener('change', drawUlamSpiral);

  resetBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {
    gridSlider.value = '100';
    showNumbers.checked = false;
    highlightDiagonals.checked = false;
    colorScheme.value = 'classic';
    drawUlamSpiral();
  });

  // Initial draw
  drawUlamSpiral();
</script>
